{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5284ac9-5661-4bba-9574-69cf548ca037","content":"To switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC), you need to make these changes:\n\n**1. On nuget.org** — configure a trusted publisher for your package:\n- Go to your package → Manage → Publishing → Add Trusted Publisher\n- Set the repository owner, name, workflow file path, and optionally environment/refs\n\n**2. In your workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Install .NET SDK, build, pack...\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write`\n- Remove `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` from the push command\n- No secret needed — the GitHub OIDC token is used automatically\n- If you configured an environment on nuget.org, add `environment: <name>` to the job\n\n**3. Clean up** — once verified, delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings.\n\nWould you like me to look at your actual workflow file and make the changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3505c647-8aeb-478d-b213-787fbb740258","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about switching from using a NuGet API key (stored as a secret) to NuGet trusted publishing via OIDC in their GitHub Actions workflow. This is a general knowledge question about GitHub Actions and NuGet publishing - I don't need to search the codebase for this since it's asking for guidance on a workflow change.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about what's needed to switch to NuGet trusted publishing with OIDC.","outputTokens":446,"requestId":"102A:9A895:29885C2:2DD30C8:69FD343D"},"id":"0e7bd858-2167-4e7b-ad70-e4254d2e57d1","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:31.929Z","parentId":"8a84c911-cf71-47